Don't use --clobber on ARM toolchain bots

The "sync" stages take 15 minutes on the fastest bot, and dominate
the time of most runs.  Until we refactor the way we handle the git
stuff, the simplest way to avoid repeating 'git clone' from scratch
every time is just to turn off the --clobber behavior.  All the actual
builds are still done entirely from scratch anyway.

BUG= https://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3086
TEST= trybots

